ProtoDefines:
. "A subset $S$ of $\R^n$ is \term{ connected } if it is 
   impossible to represent $S$ as the union of two disjoint 
   nonempty sets such that neither contains a limit point of 
   the other; that is, if $S$ cannot be expressed as $S=A\cup 
   B$, where \begin{equation} A\ne\emptyset,\quad 
   B\ne\emptyset,\quad\overline{A}\cap B= \emptyset, \quad 
   and\quad A\cap\overline{B}=\emptyset. \end{equation} If $S$ 
   can be expressed in this way, then $S$ is \term{ disconnected 
   }."
